.TH SHOW 1 "April 2026" "show 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
show \- pure assembly file viewer with syntax highlighting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B show
[\fIfile\fR]
.br
.B show
\-\-lines \fIM-N\fR [\-\-width \fIW\fR] \fIfile\fR
.br
\fIcommand\fR | \fBshow\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B show
is a file viewer written in x86_64 Linux assembly with syntax highlighting
for 20+ programming languages. No libc, no runtime, pure syscalls.
Single static binary (38KB).
.PP
Three operating modes:
.TP
.B Pager mode
(default when stdout is a terminal) Full-screen viewer with scrolling,
line numbers, and a status bar. Uses the alternate screen buffer.
.TP
.B Cat mode
(when stdout is a pipe) Outputs all lines with syntax highlighting.
Works like
.BR bat (1)
or
.BR cat (1)
with colors.
.TP
.B Pane mode
(with \-\-lines flag) Outputs a specific range of lines with highlighting.
No interactive controls. Designed for embedding in TUI applications.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-lines \fIM-N\fR
Output only lines M through N (1-indexed). Enables pane mode.
.TP
.B \-\-width \fIW\fR
Set output width for pane mode.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
In pager mode:
.TP
.B j, Down
Scroll down one line.
.TP
.B k, Up
Scroll up one line.
.TP
.B Space, PgDn
Scroll down one page.
.TP
.B b, PgUp
Scroll up one page.
.TP
.B g, Home
Go to top of file.
.TP
.B G, End
Go to end of file.
.TP
.B l
Toggle line numbers.
.TP
.B Left, Right
Horizontal scroll.
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.SH LANGUAGES
Syntax highlighting is supported for:
Assembly (.asm, .s),
C/C++ (.c, .h, .cpp, .hpp, .cc),
C# (.cs),
Forth (.fth, .4th, .forth),
Go (.go),
Java (.java),
JavaScript/TypeScript (.js, .ts, .jsx, .tsx),
Julia (.jl),
Lua (.lua),
Python (.py),
Ruby (.rb, .gemspec),
Rust (.rs),
Shell (.sh, .bash, .zsh, .fish),
XRPN (.xrpn),
JSON (.json),
YAML (.yaml, .yml),
TOML (.toml),
Markdown (.md),
Config (.conf, .cfg, .ini).
.PP
Files without extensions are identified by shebang lines
(e.g., #!/usr/bin/env ruby).
.SH COLOR SCHEME
Keywords (197, hot pink),
Strings (78, green),
Comments (242, gray),
Numbers (141, purple),
Types (81, cyan),
Functions (148, yellow-green),
Operators (248, light gray).
.SH FILES
.B show
reads files via mmap (zero-copy). Pipe input is buffered up to 1MB.
.SH PART OF
.B CHasm
(CHange to ASM) \- a suite of tools rewritten in pure assembly.
See also
.BR bare (1).
